Breadcrumbs
----------------------
It is a navigation scheme which indicates the current page's location to the user within a website or an application.

use the class .breadcrumb on ol

default breadcrumb separator is '/' but we can create our own separator using css.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <!-- <style>
.breadcrumb-item + .breadcrumb-item::before
{
content: ">";
}
</style> -->
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>breadcrumbs</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../node_modules/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"
        integrity="sha384-YvpcrYf0tY3lHB60NNkmXc5s9fDVZLESaAA55NDzOxhy9GkcIdslK1eN7N6jIeHz"
        crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container">
        <nav>
            <ol class=" breadcrumb">
                <li class="breadcrumb-item">
                    <a href="#">Products</a>
                </li>
                <li class="breadcrumb-item">
                    <a href="#">Customers</a>
                </li>
                <li class="breadcrumb-item active">
                    Orders
                </li>
            </ol>
        </nav>
    </div>
</body>

</html>
